Citation.sTitle: Measurement and Correlation of Solubilities of Cefpirome Sulfate in Aqueous Alcohol Solution between (278.15 and 308.15) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubilities of cefpirome sulfate in water + (methanol, ethanol, 1-propanol, or 2-propanol) solvent mixtures have been measured using a dynamic method at temperature ranging from (278.15 to 318.15) K at atmospheric pressure. A solubility equation was proposed and verified by experimental results. The dissolution enthalpy and dissolution entropy have been calculated from the solubility data. The interactions between solute and solvent were discussed.
